---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';

const updated = '2026-05-24';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description={`How ${site.name} handles personal information on this website.`}
>
  <section class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 pt-12 pb-16">
    <p class="text-sm uppercase tracking-wider text-[var(--color-accent-2)]">Legal</p>
    <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl mt-2 tracking-wide">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="text-xs text-[var(--color-text-dim)] mt-2">Last updated: {updated}</p>

    <aside class="mt-6 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-accent)] bg-[var(--color-surface)] px-5 py-4 text-sm">
      <p class="font-display tracking-wide text-base mb-2">In short</p>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-text)]">
        This site sets no cookies of its own, runs no analytics, and embeds
        no tracking scripts. Cloudflare sets one strictly-necessary security
        cookie for bot protection. The Twitch player is click-to-load — no
        request is made to Twitch until you press play.
      </p>
    </aside>

    <div class="prose mt-8 text-[var(--color-text)] leading-relaxed space-y-5">
      <p>
        This site is operated by Najdorf Esports (the "Organization"). The legal entity
        behind the Organization is being formalized; this notice will be updated to
        name the operating company once registration is complete.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mt-8 tracking-wide">Cookies and tracking</h2>
      <p>
        This site sets <strong>no cookies of its own.</strong> No analytics,
        no advertising trackers, no fingerprinting scripts, no first-party
        tracking pixels. Pages are static HTML, CSS, and a small amount of
        vanilla JavaScript for the match countdown, mobile navigation, and a
        client-side hero swap on match day. Nothing on the site reads or
        writes to <code>document.cookie</code>, <code>localStorage</code>,
        <code>sessionStorage</code>, or <code>IndexedDB</code>.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our hosting platform (Cloudflare Pages) sets one strictly-necessary,
        first-party cookie named <code>__cf_bm</code> on requests to this
        domain. It is a 30-minute bot-management token used only for
        infrastructure security — it is not shared with us, is not used for
        cross-site tracking, and is exempt from cookie-consent requirements
        under the "strictly necessary" exception in EU ePrivacy guidance.
        See
        <a href="https://developers.cloudflare.com/fundamentals/reference/policies-compliances/cloudflare-cookies/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cloudflare's cookie reference</a>
        for details.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cloudflare additionally retains short-term access logs (IP, user
        agent, URL) for security and abuse-prevention. We do not link these
        logs to any personal identity and do not use them for marketing.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mt-8 tracking-wide">Fonts</h2>
      <p>
        Display and body fonts (Anton, Inter) are served directly from this
        domain. No font requests are sent to Google, Adobe, or other third-party
        font CDNs.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mt-8 tracking-wide">Embedded video player</h2>
      <p>
        During an active match window (roughly 30 minutes before kickoff
        through three hours after), the home page shows a click-to-load
        Twitch placeholder. <strong>No request is made to Twitch until you
        click the play button.</strong> If you never click it, your browser
        never contacts twitch.tv from this page and Twitch sets no cookies
        on your device.
      </p>
      <p>
        Once you click to load the player, Twitch may set its own cookies
        and collect usage data per its own policies. We do not control
        those cookies or receive their contents. See
        <a href="https://www.twitch.tv/p/legal/privacy-notice/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Twitch's Privacy Notice</a>
        for details.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mt-8 tracking-wide">Outbound links</h2>
      <p>
        Player profiles link to third-party sites (Twitter / X, Twitch,
        Liquipedia) when those handles are available. Clicking an outbound link
        takes you to that site, whose own privacy practices apply once you arrive.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mt-8 tracking-wide">Email contact</h2>
      <p>
        If you email us at {site.contactEmail}, we will store the contents of your
        message and your email address for as long as is reasonably needed to
        respond and keep records of the correspondence.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mt-8 tracking-wide">Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        Depending on where you live, you may have the right to request a copy of any
        personal data we hold about you, request that we delete it, or ask us to
        correct it. Reach us at {site.contactEmail}.
      </p>

      <h2 class="font-display text-2xl mt-8 tracking-wide">Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We will update the "Last updated" date above when this policy changes.
        Material changes will be announced in the news section.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style is:global>
  .prose p { margin-bottom: 1em; }
  .prose a { color: var(--color-accent-2); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .prose a:hover { color: var(--color-accent); }
</style>
